<TEXT>
declaring the world has lived too long 
in the shadow of chemical warfare president bush offered monday 
to slash us stocks of such weapons more than 80 percent provided 
the soviet union reduces to an equal level 
bushs proposal in his first speech to the un general 
assembly as president was designed to spur a 40nation conference 
in geneva to ban chemical weapons entirely within 10 years 
he also used his appearance to salute freedoms march around 
the world in hungary poland latin america and africa and to 
